l_2
L=\log p( {\bf y} | {\bf x}) = \sum_i \log p(y_i | x_i) 
\log p(y_i | x_i)= a + b \, d_i 
d_i = | x_i -y_i|
b=2 \epsilon -1 <0 
a=1-\epsilon
L = n a + b \sum d_i
\sum d_i =\|{\bf x}-{\bf y}\|_1
\log p(y_i | x_i) = s + t \,d_i^2
t<0
\|{\bf x}-{\bf y}\|_2
\log p(y_i | x_i) =  g(|x_i-y_i|^k)
g : {\mathbb R}_{\ge 0} \to {\mathbb R}
k
\hat x =\arg \min_{x\in C}\|x-y\|_k
